{"questionId":"9076511","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Data from distant galaxies are shown on the graph.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4761/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-12_om_17.19.55.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/SP3/ENG/TZ2/12\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>On the graph, one galaxy is labelled A. Determine the size of the universe, relative to&nbsp;its present size, when light from the galaxy labelled A was emitted.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>z</em>&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>&nbsp;= <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{v}{c}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>v</mi>\n    <mi>c</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span><strong>»</strong>&nbsp;=&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{4.6 \\times {{10}^4} \\times {{10}^3}}}{{3.00 \\times {{10}^8}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>4.6</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>4</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>3.00</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>8</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> = 0.15</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{R}{{{R_0}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>R</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>R</mi>\n          <mn>0</mn>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> =&nbsp;<strong>«</strong><em>z</em> + 1<strong>»</strong> = 1.15</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{R_0}}}{R}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>R</mi>\n          <mn>0</mn>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>R</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> =&nbsp;<strong>«</strong><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{{1.15}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1.15</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> =<strong>»</strong>&nbsp;0.87</p>\n<p><strong><em>OR</em></strong></p>\n<p>87% of the present size</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076511","referenceCode":"18M.3.SL.TZ2.c","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"On the graph, one galaxy is labelled A. Determine the size of the universe, relative to its present size, when light from the galaxy labelled A was emitted.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option D: Astrophysics","Option D: Astrophysics","Option D: Astrophysics (Core topics)","D.3 – Cosmology","Option D: Astrophysics","Option D: Astrophysics (Core topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}